Did they recast the role just to have a foil with which to prop up interest in the tired Bridge pairing? He could hand Thomas his head on a platter and be disgusted with his sonbut at the same time he holds him accountable, Rich could also show some self reflection by pointing out to Brooke that the reason why he believed she made the call was because on some level she really does dislike his children and they clearly don't like her, a position which is truly untenable for him as a man trying to balance his role within a marriage with his role as a father within a family unit, even if his children are now adults. He doesn't have to even marry Taylor now, and in fact it would show real maturity if he instead went back to Taylor and said that he didn't want to marry her until she felt the kind of confidence in him that he has always felt in her love, saying that this has long been a problem in their marriage and he doesn't want it to be a factor in their future. He could point to their earlier years together and admit to her that because he never made a truly firm decision between her and Brooke that his divided heart always left Taylor feeling insecure and vulnerable in the marriage and if their marriage had any true weakness it was the fact that he never was able to give Taylor that comfort level and that he now wants to do better.
